5
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:15,724
(CLEARS THROAT)

6
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:18,977
WILLIAM: Welcome back.

7
00:00:19,061 --> 00:00:21,063
(MUSIC BOX PLAYING
BIZET'S <i>TOREADOR SONG)</i>

8
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:25,442
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
boys and girls,</i>

9
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:27,903
<i>are you ready
to start the show?</i>

10
00:00:27,986 --> 00:00:29,279
CHILDREN: <i>Yeah!</i>

11
00:00:29,363 --> 00:00:31,323
WILLIAM: <i>Are you ready
to start the show?</i>

12
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:34,243
CHILDREN: <i>Yeah!</i>

13
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:37,037
WILLIAM: <i>Don't forget to
stay around till the very end</i>

14
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:40,707
{\an8}<i>for a great big surprise.</i>

15
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,043
{\an8}<i>Here we go!</i>

16
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:46,588
<i>Count with me now.</i>

17
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,675
WILLIAM AND CHILDREN:
<i>Ten, nine,</i>

18
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:53,595
<i>eight, seven, six,</i>

19
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:57,015
<i>five, four, three,</i>

20
00:00:57,099 --> 00:00:59,351
<i>two, one.</i>

21
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:00,852
WILLIAM: <i>Showtime!</i>

22
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:04,147
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

23
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:06,233
(CHILDREN CHEERING)

24
00:01:07,234 --> 00:01:09,236
(EXCITED CHATTER)

25
00:01:15,284 --> 00:01:16,660
WOMAN: All right, this one?

26
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:19,913
CHILD: Come on!
CHILD 2: So close!

27
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:21,123
{\an8}(BOY CHATTERS)

28
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,710
Oh, cool!
(CHILD SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

29
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:30,507
MAN: Hey.

30
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:34,136
WOMAN: Thank you, honey.

31
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:35,220
Bye.

32
00:01:46,273 --> 00:01:48,275
(MUSIC FADES)

33
00:01:48,859 --> 00:01:51,570
You seriously just gonna sit
here till the trapdoors open?

34
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:54,281
Leave her alone. She does
this every time she's here.

35
00:01:55,157 --> 00:01:56,158
Come on.

36
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,416
GIRL: You look like someone
who could use a Freddy Fazcola.

37
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,128
(SLURPING)

38
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:10,589
Ew.

39
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,632
Tastes like gasoline.
(CHUCKLES)

40
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:16,720
GIRL: It doesn't come out
for a while.

41
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:19,931
{\an8}Why don't you come back to
the table and hang out with us?

42
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:21,350
They don't
want me there.

43
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:23,268
No one does.

44
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:25,354
You just got
a bad roll of the dice.

45
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:26,730
Things will get better.

46
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,985
She's the only one
I can rely on.

47
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,988
She's the only one
who's always here for me.

48
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:38,658
That... thing down there

49
00:02:38,742 --> 00:02:40,827
isn't your
spirit parent

50
00:02:40,911 --> 00:02:42,996
or whatever
you think it is.

51
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,082
And it'll still
be there

52
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,084
even if you go have
a piece of cake first.

53
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,878
CHILDREN: (SINGING)
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

54
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:52,297
<i>(MANIAC BY</i> MICHAEL SEMBELLO PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS) CHILDREN: Happy birthday!

55
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:53,673
(APPLAUDING)

56
