business, it's brought it all back.

995
00:59:57,844 --> 00:59:59,304
{\an8}It's an abomination,

996
00:59:59,387 --> 01:00:00,806
{\an8}people celebrating
that place.

997
01:00:00,889 --> 01:00:02,849
{\an8}That's <i>why</i> I posted
those flyers.

998
01:00:03,475 --> 01:00:05,769
People need to know
the truth. Wait, what...

999
01:00:07,521 --> 01:00:10,190
Where... where is this?
What is this?

1000
01:00:10,273 --> 01:00:12,442
(INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING)
It's the... the river ride.

1001
01:00:12,526 --> 01:00:14,110
It was one
of Charlotte's favorites.

1002
01:00:14,820 --> 01:00:16,112
But I... I've been
to Freddy's.

1003
01:00:16,196 --> 01:00:17,572
There's not a...
a river ride.

1004
01:00:17,656 --> 01:00:19,199
There was only one
at the first Freddy's.

1005
01:00:19,282 --> 01:00:21,451
None of the later
locations had one.

1006
01:00:22,035 --> 01:00:23,453
First Freddy's?

1007
01:00:26,081 --> 01:00:27,123
Abby drew this.

1008
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:29,459
Uh, can...
can I use your phone?

1009
01:00:29,543 --> 01:00:31,294
Yeah, of course.
It's over there.

1010
01:00:32,963 --> 01:00:34,673
(PHONE RINGING)

1011
01:00:35,924 --> 01:00:37,092
BETTE: <i>Hello?</i>

1012
01:00:37,676 --> 01:00:39,094
MIKE: (OVER PHONE) <i>And
you're sure she isn't there?</i>

1013
01:00:39,177 --> 01:00:40,345
I'm so sorry, sir.

1014
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:43,974
Apparently, there was some
sort of incident and she left.

1015
01:00:44,057 --> 01:00:46,017
But if you'd like, I can
call the... (CLANKS)

1016
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:48,228
(DIAL TONE DRONING)
(SCOFFS)

1017
01:00:49,855 --> 01:00:50,856
What an asshole.

1018
01:00:52,899 --> 01:00:54,109
Is everything all right?

1019
01:00:54,192 --> 01:00:56,903
I, uh... I don't...
I... I don't know. Um...

1020
01:00:57,946 --> 01:00:59,239
I think my sister...

1021
01:01:01,032 --> 01:01:02,450
I think she's here.

1022
01:01:03,618 --> 01:01:05,245
One-two-five...

1023
01:01:05,328 --> 01:01:07,622
two-five...
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1024
01:01:07,706 --> 01:01:10,166
I made this music box for
Charlotte when she was just a baby.

1025
01:01:10,250 --> 01:01:12,002
The music,
it helped her sleep.

1026
01:01:12,085 --> 01:01:14,796
I know this might sound
crazy, but if you go back there,

1027
01:01:14,880 --> 01:01:16,172
would you leave it
for her?

1028
01:01:18,717 --> 01:01:20,051
Uh, yeah.

1029
01:01:21,928 --> 01:01:23,013
Thank you.

1030
01:01:25,765 --> 01:01:28,393
(BROODING MUSIC PLAYING)

1031
01:01:31,187 --> 01:01:32,898
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

1032
01:01:34,232 --> 01:01:35,567
(TIRES SCREECH)

1033
01:01:38,278 --> 01:01:39,905
(ENGINE IDLING)

1034
01:01:44,534 --> 01:01:45,535
Abby?

1035
01:01:48,830 --> 01:01:51,166
(DOORS RATTLING)

1036
01:01:51,249 --> 01:01:52,250
(SHOUTS) Abby?

1037
01:02:03,637 --> 01:02:05,472
(THUDDING)

1038
01:02:07,557 --> 01:02:09,517
(GRUNTING AND PANTING)

1039
01:02:10,894 --> 01:02:11,895
(GASPS)

1040
01:02:12,854 --> 01:02:13,855
(GRUNTS)

1041
01:02:14,773 --> 01:02:16,024
(PANTING)

1042
01:02:22,238 --> 01:02:24,157
(MENACING MUSIC PLAYING)
(GASPS IN FEAR)

1043
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:25,659
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1044
01:02:48,139 --> 01:02:49,307
(DISTANT CLANK)

1045
01:02:49,391 --> 01:02:50,392
(SOFTLY) Abby?

1046
01:02:50,850 --> 01:02:51,851
(DISTANT CLANK)

1047
01:02:59,651 --> 01:03:01,653
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
(INDISTINCT CHATTER INSIDE)

1048
01:03:02,946 --> 01:03:04,698
(CLATTERING)

1049
01:03:11,871 --> 01:03:13,248
(CHUCKLING)

1050
01:03:14,124 --> 01:03:16,209
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING IN
DISTANCE) CHILD: Whoa! A giant robot.

1051
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:17,377
MR. BERG: Excuse me.
Pardon me.

1052
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:18,795
CHILD 2: Look, it's Chica!
Excuse me. Clear out.

1053
01:03:19,504 --> 01:03:20,880
CHILD 3: Whoa. What's
going on over here?

1054
01:03:20,964 --> 01:03:23,466
Mr. Berg, this is my new
science fair project.

1055
01:03:24,676 --> 01:03:28,471
{\an8}<i>Mr. Berg, I've heard
so much about you.</i>

1056
01:03:31,016 --> 01:03:33,184
Is this a joke,
Ms. Schmidt?

1057
01:03:34,227 --> 01:03:37,522
Putting someone in a suit and
passing it off as your own work?

1058
01:03:38,023 --> 01:03:40,025
You're an embarrassment
to our class

1059
01:03:40,108 --> 01:03:41,943
and to our school,
Ms. Schmidt.

1060
01:03:42,027 --> 01:03:43,653
Now, take your
freak-show friend,

1061
01:03:43,737 --> 01:03:45,655
and get out
of my science fair,

1062
01:03:46,239 --> 01:03:48,450
before you
lose us the title.

1063
01:03:52,871 --> 01:03:54,080
I'm sorry, Chica.

1064
01:03:54,831 --> 01:03:56,916
<i>There is nothing
to be sorry about.</i>

1065
01:03:59,169 --> 01:04:01,296
{\an8}<i>How about
I go talk to him?</i>

1066
01:04:02,172 --> 01:04:03,173
{\an8}What are you gonna say?

1067
01:04:03,256 --> 01:04:07,343
{\an8}<i>I just want to see what's
going on inside of his head.</i>

1068
01:04:08,178 --> 01:04:10,055
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)
CHILD: Oh, whoa.

1069
01:04:11,598 --> 01:04:12,599
No.

1070
01:04:13,308 --> 01:04:14,476
I'm on my way.

1071
01:04:14,559 --> 01:04:17,020
I... I just left my
keys in my office.

1072
01:04:18,188 --> 01:04:19,189
Again.

1073
01:04:20,356 --> 01:04:21,941
(BOTH YELLING, LAUGHING)
(MR. BERG YELPS)

1074
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:23,610
This part of the building
is closed!

1075
01:04:24,235 --> 01:04:25,779
Now, get out of here...
(BABBLING MOCKINGLY)

1076
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:27,489
...before I have
you both expelled.

1077
01:04:28,198 --> 01:04:30,533
(SIGHS) Oh, geez.

1078
01:04:32,535 --> 01:04:33,995
(KEYS JINGLING)
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1079
01:04:34,079 --> 01:04:35,622
(SOFT ELECTRICAL HUM
IN DISTANCE)

1080
01:04:37,874 --> 01:04:39,667
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING
IN DISTANCE)

1081
01:04:51,596 --> 01:04:53,473
(LIGHTS CLINKING)

1082
01:04:55,725 --> 01:04:57,560
(MUTTERING)

1083
01:05:01,231 --> 01:05:02,524
(MR. BERG SIGHS)

1084
01:05:08,988 --> 01:05:10,949
(ELECTRICAL HUMMING
IN DISTANCE)

1085
01:05:12,700 --> 01:05:14,702
(FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING)

1086
01:05:27,257 --> 01:05:28,883
(GASPS AND SCREAMS)

1087
01:05:29,509 --> 01:05:32,428
(GLASS SHATTERS)
(YELLING)

1088
01:05:32,512 --> 01:05:35,557
(GROANING AND YELPING)

1089
01:05:36,141 --> 01:05:37,725
(GASPS)

1090
01:05:37,809 --> 01:05:40,019
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

1091
01:05:43,106 --> 01:05:45,608
(MR. BERG GROANING, SOBBING)

1092
01:05:49,195 --> 01:05:51,281
(GROANING AND WHIMPERING)

1093
01:05:52,365 --> 01:05:54,117
(SCREAMS, YELPS)

1094
01:05:54,200 --> 01:05:55,952
(GROANS AND THUDS)

1095
01:05:58,705 --> 01:06:00,039
(WHIMPERING)

1096
01:06:01,291 --> 01:06:02,584
(SOBBING)

1097
01:06:02,667 --> 01:06:04,252
CHICA: <i>I would like
to talk to you</i>

1098
01:06:04,335 --> 01:06:07,714
<i>about Abby's project,
Mr. Berg.</i>

1099
01:06:07,797 --> 01:06:09,883
(ELECTRICAL HUMMING)

1100
01:06:09,966 --> 01:06:11,968
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

1101
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:21,311
(SCREAMING)

1102
01:06:21,394 --> 01:06:23,688
I'll give her an "A!"
(WHIMPERING)

1103
01:06:23,771 --> 01:06:25,815
You... you... (PANTING)
...you want test answers?

1104
01:06:25,899 --> 01:06:29,444
(SOBBING) I'll... I'll give
you answers to the next test.

1105
01:06:29,527 --> 01:06:32,238
(GROANING)

1106
01:06:33,406 --> 01:06:35,700
(SCREAMING)

1107
01:06:36,492 --> 01:06:42,498
{\an8}<i>What I want is to see what's
going on inside of your head.</i>

1108
01:06:42,582 --> 01:06:43,958
(MR. BERG GROANING)

1109
01:06:45,376 --> 01:06:46,794
(SCREAMING)

1110
01:06:48,713 --> 01:06:50,673
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)
(SKULL CREAKING)

1111
01:06:54,427 --> 01:06:56,346
(HEAD SPLATS)
(BODY THUDS)

1112
01:06:58,681 --> 01:07:00,308
{\an8}<i>Just as I thought.</i>

1113
01:07:02,644 --> 01:07:04,354
{\an8}<i>Nothing in there
at all.</i>

1114
01:07:06,689 --> 01:07:08,691
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1115
01:07:11,152 --> 01:07:12,153
Abby?

1116
01:07:18,201 --> 01:07:20,453
(THUDDING)

1117
01:07:30,296 --> 01:07:31,297
Abby?

1118
01:07:31,381 --> 01:07:34,300
(LOUD THUDDING)

1119
01:07:36,761 --> 01:07:38,763
(KNOB RATTLES)
(GRUNTS, PANTS)

1120
01:07:38,846 --> 01:07:39,847
Vanessa.
(GROANS)

1121
01:07:41,057 --> 01:07:42,225
(WHIMPERS)
MIKE: Are you okay?

1122
01:07:42,308 --> 01:07:44,352
VANESSA: (GRUNTING)
I'm okay.

1123
01:07:44,978 --> 01:07:46,854
What's going on?
Where... where's Abby?

1124
01:07:46,938 --> 01:07:48,731
VANESSA: I don't know
where she is exactly, but...

1125
01:07:48,815 --> 01:07:52,568
(PANTING) ...she left
with them, the animatronics.

1126
01:07:52,652 --> 01:07:54,404
I just saw the animatronics
in... in a back room.

1127
01:07:55,321 --> 01:07:58,241
No, those are just prototypes
used for spare parts.

1128
01:07:58,741 --> 01:07:59,742
It's Charlotte.

1129
01:08:00,451 --> 01:08:01,744
She's behind everything.

1130
01:08:02,328 --> 01:08:04,455
I think Abby
might be in danger.

1131
01:08:04,956 --> 01:08:07,000
We need to get
to the security office.

1132
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:08,710
It's the only <i>way</i>
I know how to help her.

1133
01:08:09,419 --> 01:08:10,420
Come on.

1134
01:08:10,962 --> 01:08:12,422
(VANESSA GROANS, PANTS)

1135
01:08:15,550 --> 01:08:18,511
I know you don't want to,
but you have to trust me.

1136
01:08:19,512 --> 01:08:21,514
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1137
01:08:24,309 --> 01:08:25,310
Okay.

1138
01:08:27,603 --> 01:08:28,771
(GIRL LAUGHING IN DISTANCE)

1139
01:08:30,273 --> 01:08:31,316
Is there another way?

1140
01:08:34,694 --> 01:08:35,903
VANESSA: (PANTING)
Come on.

1141
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:41,200
I don't understand. Are...
are the ghost kids here now?

1142
01:08:41,284 --> 01:08:45,413
No, there's just one ghost
here... in the marionette.

1143
01:08:46,706 --> 01:08:47,707
Charlotte.

1144
01:08:47,790 --> 01:08:50,877
After she was killed, I would
sometimes still see her here.

1145
01:08:52,879 --> 01:08:55,590
VANESSA:
<i>She seemed stuck</i>

1146
01:08:55,673 --> 01:08:58,968
<i>in the last emotion
before she died.</i>

1147
01:08:59,052 --> 01:09:00,970
(SCREAMING)

1148
01:09:01,054 --> 01:09:02,055
Rage.

1149
01:09:05,224 --> 01:09:07,769
But there's this music box
that kept her asleep.

1150
01:09:12,607 --> 01:09:14,734
(GENTLE MELODY PLAYING)

1151
01:09:16,694 --> 01:09:18,571
(RUSTLING)

1152
01:09:20,531 --> 01:09:23,326
(MECHANICAL RATTLING)

1153
01:09:30,249 --> 01:09:32,752
<i>I put her to sleep
with this music box, but...</i>

1154
01:09:34,128 --> 01:09:36,464
something or someone
broke it.

1155
01:09:37,423 --> 01:09:38,508
Wait.

1156
01:09:38,591 --> 01:09:40,176
Henry just gave me
a music box.

1157
01:09:40,259 --> 01:09:41,969
(WATER SPLASHING)
(GASPS)

1158
01:09:43,763 --> 01:09:45,181
Maybe coming this <i>way</i>
was a bad idea.

1159
01:09:46,140 --> 01:09:47,141
Hurry.

1160
01:09:47,225 --> 01:09:48,601
(YELPS)
(SCREAMS)

1161
01:09:49,435 --> 01:09:50,436
Mike.

1162
01:09:51,437 --> 01:09:53,523
(BURBLING)

1163
01:09:53,606 --> 01:09:55,608
(MENACING MUSIC PLAYING)

1164
01:10:00,905 --> 01:10:02,198
Here.

1165
01:10:02,281 --> 01:10:03,783
Here. Grab my hand.

1166
01:10:11,749 --> 01:10:12,917
Mike!

1167
01:10:16,796 --> 01:10:17,797
Come on.

1168
01:10:23,803 --> 01:10:25,263
Okay. Come on.

1169
01:10:25,346 --> 01:10:26,889
Come on, come on,
come on.

1170
01:10:29,308 --> 01:10:30,309
Where are you?

1171
01:10:33,271 --> 01:10:34,981
Vanessa, what are we doing here?
How do... how do we find Abby?

1172
01:10:35,731 --> 01:10:37,567
I'm trying to pull up
the tracker.

1173
01:10:37,650 --> 01:10:39,819
Abby thinks these
animatronics are her friends,

1174
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:40,903
but they're not.

1175
01:10:40,987 --> 01:10:43,322
They're being wirelessly
controlled by the marionette.

1176
01:10:43,406 --> 01:10:44,490
By Charlotte.

1177
01:10:44,574 --> 01:10:46,242
What does she want?

1178
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:50,371
My father killed her,
but she doesn't blame him.

1179
01:10:50,455 --> 01:10:52,206
She blames the parents.

1180
01:10:52,915 --> 01:10:53,916
All parents.

1181
01:10:54,000 --> 01:10:55,918
Okay. What does she want
with my sister?

1182
01:10:56,002 --> 01:10:58,004
It seems like
the marionette needs

1183
01:10:58,754 --> 01:11:00,548
something or someone
to bond to

1184
01:11:00,631 --> 01:11:01,924
in order to move around.

1185
01:11:02,008 --> 01:11:04,427
I'm afraid it might
target Abby next.

1186
01:11:04,510 --> 01:11:05,636
So there's
four animatronics,

1187
01:11:05,720 --> 01:11:07,346
and we don't know
which one has Abby.

1188
01:11:10,016 --> 01:11:12,268
They're all out because the
perimeter locks were disabled.

1189
01:11:12,351 --> 01:11:15,313
It's a system that drains the
animatronics of their power

1190
01:11:15,396 --> 01:11:16,939
the moment they leave
the building.

1191
01:11:17,023 --> 01:11:20,067
But we can find them once
we get their trackers working.

1192
01:11:20,151 --> 01:11:21,527
{\an8}MIKE: Wait.
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

1193
01:11:21,611 --> 01:11:22,904
{\an8}Did you say
that the marionette

1194
01:11:22,987 --> 01:11:24,280
{\an8}controls them
wirelessly?

1195
01:11:24,363 --> 01:11:25,364
Yeah.

1196
01:11:28,701 --> 01:11:30,786
Get up. Look, you... you
go... you go into town,

1197
01:11:30,870 --> 01:11:32,079
find Charlotte
and just try to buy me

1198
01:11:32,163 --> 01:11:33,164
as much time as you can,

1199
01:11:33,247 --> 01:11:35,625
and I'll try to disconnect
the signal from here.

1200
01:11:36,709 --> 01:11:38,044
Okay. Here.

1201
01:11:38,127 --> 01:11:39,795
We can use these.

1202
01:11:39,879 --> 01:11:42,298
Mike, I should have
told you about her.

1203
01:11:42,381 --> 01:11:44,383
I should have told you
about this place.

1204
01:11:44,467 --> 01:11:46,552
I... I, um...

1205
01:11:47,887 --> 01:11:49,555
(CHILDLIKE GIGGLING
IN DISTANCE)

1206
01:11:51,307 --> 01:11:53,059
Hey, don't worry about that
right now, okay? Just... just go.

1207
01:11:53,142 --> 01:11:54,143
Please.
Okay.

1208
01:11:57,605 --> 01:11:58,898
Hey, how do I close
the door?

1209
01:11:58,981 --> 01:12:00,233
There isn't a door.

1210
01:12:01,275 --> 01:12:02,401
There isn't a door?

1211
01:12:05,154 --> 01:12:06,989
What kind of idiot
designed this place?

1212
01:12:10,409 --> 01:12:12,370
All right, where the
hell are you guys?

1213
01:12:12,453 --> 01:12:13,996
(EXHALES) Okay.

1214
01:12:14,580 --> 01:12:16,165
Maybe no one
will notice them.

1215
01:12:17,250 --> 01:12:19,752
(<i>THE BOMB!</i> BY KENNY DOPE
PRESENTS THE BUCKETHEADS PLAYING)

1216
01:12:19,835 --> 01:12:21,295
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

1217
01:12:35,017 --> 01:12:37,353
Dude,
that costume is...

1218
01:12:37,436 --> 01:12:38,771
Legendary.

1219
01:12:38,854 --> 01:12:39,897
I don't know.

1220
01:12:40,690 --> 01:12:42,358
Seems kind
of fake to me.

1221
01:12:42,441 --> 01:12:43,985
Don't be rude.
What?

1222
01:12:44,068 --> 01:12:45,861
I mean, it just looks
like a toy, is all.

1223
01:12:46,696 --> 01:12:48,864
Hey, we're on the <i>way</i> to the
costume contest. You want to come?

1224
01:12:50,283 --> 01:12:53,244
<i>I do, but first,</i>

1225
01:12:53,327 --> 01:12:57,456
<i>I have to go pull the heads
off some very bad people.</i>

1226
01:12:57,540 --> 01:12:59,000
Right on.
(CHUCKLES)

1227
01:12:59,083 --> 01:13:00,710
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

1228
01:13:02,795 --> 01:13:03,796
He wins.

1229
01:13:04,505 --> 01:13:05,506
Yeah.

1230
01:13:06,382 --> 01:13:08,384
(MENACING MUSIC PLAYING)
(CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

1231
01:13:26,277 --> 01:13:27,653
Okay.

1232
01:13:27,737 --> 01:13:29,071
Here goes nothing.

1233
01:13:31,282 --> 01:13:33,701
(BEEPING)

