1473
01:27:48,513 --> 01:27:49,931
TOY VOICE: <i>No, silly.</i>

1474
01:27:50,015 --> 01:27:52,267
<i>It's me, Abby.</i>

1475
01:27:53,101 --> 01:27:54,561
(LAUGHING)
(SCREAMS)

1476
01:27:54,644 --> 01:27:55,937
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

1477
01:27:56,021 --> 01:27:57,606
VANESSA: Charlotte,
what have you done?

1478
01:28:05,739 --> 01:28:08,533
ABBY'S VOICE: Come out,
come out, wherever you are.

1479
01:28:08,617 --> 01:28:11,244
Vanessa.

1480
01:28:11,328 --> 01:28:14,831
The adults in your life
betrayed you, too.

1481
01:28:14,915 --> 01:28:17,417
They don't deserve
your protection.

1482
01:28:17,501 --> 01:28:19,836
You don't have
to die with them.

1483
01:28:19,920 --> 01:28:21,463
You can help me.

1484
01:28:22,339 --> 01:28:23,757
Vanessa.

1485
01:28:24,716 --> 01:28:25,926
(LAUGHS)

1486
01:28:26,009 --> 01:28:27,677
You really thought
I'd forget

1487
01:28:27,761 --> 01:28:29,721
the first rule
of hide-and-seek?

1488
01:28:31,890 --> 01:28:34,142
Always check
behind the door.

1489
01:28:42,984 --> 01:28:45,403
(PANTS, THUDS)

1490
01:28:45,487 --> 01:28:47,822
(WHIMPERING)

1491
01:28:50,659 --> 01:28:52,410
Charlotte, listen to me.

1492
01:28:52,494 --> 01:28:54,663
Abby's innocent.
Just let her go.

1493
01:28:54,746 --> 01:28:55,997
You know, Vanessa,

1494
01:28:57,082 --> 01:28:58,291
I've always wondered,

1495
01:28:59,042 --> 01:29:02,087
what exactly goes on
inside of your head?

1496
01:29:02,170 --> 01:29:05,090
(ABBY'S VOICE LAUGHING)

1497
01:29:05,173 --> 01:29:07,634
(MUSIC BOX MELODY PLAYING)
(LAUGHING STOPS)

1498
01:29:07,717 --> 01:29:09,177
(SHUDDERING)

1499
01:29:09,261 --> 01:29:11,596
ABBY'S VOICE:
No. No.

1500
01:29:15,600 --> 01:29:17,852
(SCREAMING)

1501
01:29:18,770 --> 01:29:20,522
(ABBY COUGHING)

1502
01:29:23,525 --> 01:29:26,528
(ABBY GASPING, COUGHING)

1503
01:29:28,113 --> 01:29:29,114
MIKE: Abby.

1504
01:29:31,199 --> 01:29:32,826
ABBY: Mike.
MIKE: Abby.

1505
01:29:32,909 --> 01:29:34,536
Hey. Are you okay?
(GROANS)

1506
01:29:34,619 --> 01:29:36,329
I don't know
what happened.

1507
01:29:36,413 --> 01:29:38,498
I feel sick.

1508
01:29:38,582 --> 01:29:42,377
It's like the bag of orange
gummy candies all over again.

1509
01:29:42,460 --> 01:29:43,712
MIKE: All right, can
you... can you stand up?

1510
01:29:43,795 --> 01:29:45,505
ABBY: I think so.
MIKE: Yeah? Okay.

1511
01:29:46,089 --> 01:29:47,173
Let's get out
of here.

1512
01:29:47,674 --> 01:29:48,675
Yeah.

1513
01:29:49,384 --> 01:29:51,886
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS)

1514
01:29:54,139 --> 01:29:55,515
Come on. Come on.

1515
01:29:55,599 --> 01:29:56,808
(GLASS SHATTERS)
(ABBY SCREAMS)

1516
01:29:56,891 --> 01:29:59,019
(MECHANICAL GROWLING)

1517
01:29:59,102 --> 01:30:01,146
(MENACING MUSIC PLAYING)

1518
01:30:03,898 --> 01:30:05,859
(MECHANICAL SNARLING)

1519
01:30:08,320 --> 01:30:09,571
MICHAEL: Knock, knock.
(VANESSA GASPS)

1520
01:30:12,490 --> 01:30:15,076
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
Hiya, sis.

1521
01:30:16,536 --> 01:30:17,787
Michael.

1522
01:30:17,871 --> 01:30:19,372
(INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING)

1523
01:30:19,456 --> 01:30:21,207
Vanessa, what the hell
is going on?

1524
01:30:21,291 --> 01:30:22,417
MICHAEL: Oh,
let me guess.

1525
01:30:22,500 --> 01:30:24,336
She never told you
about me.

1526
01:30:24,419 --> 01:30:25,962
(CHUCKLES)

1527
01:30:26,046 --> 01:30:27,922
That's my sister for ya.

1528
01:30:28,673 --> 01:30:31,468
She always was a little
selective with the truth.

1529
01:30:33,136 --> 01:30:34,137
I'm Michael.

1530
01:30:35,138 --> 01:30:36,806
Michael Afton.

1531
01:30:37,307 --> 01:30:39,768
I am so pleased
to finally meet you.

1532
01:30:39,851 --> 01:30:40,894
Leave them alone, Michael.

1533
01:30:40,977 --> 01:30:42,395
They haven't done
anything wrong.

1534
01:30:42,479 --> 01:30:45,273
I think our father might
strongly disagree with that.

1535
01:30:45,357 --> 01:30:46,691
Your father's dead.

1536
01:30:49,861 --> 01:30:50,862
Yeah.

1537
01:30:52,614 --> 01:30:55,033
But I'm here
to continue his legacy,

1538
01:30:55,742 --> 01:30:57,827
just in time for Fazfest.

1539
01:30:59,788 --> 01:31:01,247
That was you.

1540
01:31:01,331 --> 01:31:02,707
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

1541
01:31:04,542 --> 01:31:06,127
Well, your aunt was the one

1542
01:31:06,211 --> 01:31:08,713
who rekindled everyone's
interest in Freddy's, but...

1543
01:31:09,923 --> 01:31:13,134
(CHUCKLES) I gotta admit,
I did add fuel to the fire.

1544
01:31:13,218 --> 01:31:15,470
(LAUGHING)
It's the perfect cover.

1545
01:31:15,553 --> 01:31:17,722
I mean... (SIGHS)

1546
01:31:17,806 --> 01:31:20,308
...we're all just
gonna blend right in.

1547
01:31:20,392 --> 01:31:22,310
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1548
01:31:26,731 --> 01:31:28,608
Half of this town
will be dead by morning.

1549
01:31:28,692 --> 01:31:30,735
You can't do this.
This isn't a game.

1550
01:31:31,986 --> 01:31:32,987
Michael.

1551
01:31:33,530 --> 01:31:35,323
You can have
a normal life.

1552
01:31:35,407 --> 01:31:37,158
We could have
a normal life.

1553
01:31:38,952 --> 01:31:41,746
Vanessa, is that
what you thought?

1554
01:31:43,289 --> 01:31:45,500
You thought you
could just trade us in?

1555
01:31:46,501 --> 01:31:49,170
Betray us? Get
yourself a shiny new life?

1556
01:31:51,172 --> 01:31:53,007
You are his child.

1557
01:31:54,592 --> 01:31:56,803
You have a purpose.

1558
01:31:59,013 --> 01:32:02,475
We will always
be his.

1559
01:32:03,560 --> 01:32:04,561
Come home.

1560
01:32:08,815 --> 01:32:10,024
I am home.

1561
01:32:18,533 --> 01:32:19,534
Hmm.

1562
01:32:20,243 --> 01:32:21,369
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1563
01:32:22,454 --> 01:32:25,123
(GIGGLES) Doesn't matter
to me anyway.

1564
01:32:27,083 --> 01:32:29,210
Yeah. Break their bones.

1565
01:32:29,294 --> 01:32:31,629
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)
Crush them.

1566
01:32:31,713 --> 01:32:33,465
{\an8}(ABBY GASPS)
It's okay. It's okay.

1567
01:32:35,091 --> 01:32:36,593
(MECHANICAL SNARL)

1568
01:32:39,804 --> 01:32:42,182
(VOICE SCATTING)

1569
01:32:45,143 --> 01:32:47,187
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1570
01:32:47,270 --> 01:32:48,813
(THUDS)
(GASPS)

1571
01:32:49,647 --> 01:32:52,358
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

1572
01:32:52,442 --> 01:32:54,152
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1573
01:33:02,660 --> 01:33:05,205
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1574
01:33:16,758 --> 01:33:18,218
Freddy?

1575
01:33:18,301 --> 01:33:20,011
(GROWLS)

1576
01:33:20,094 --> 01:33:22,222
(MECHANICAL SNARLING)
(GASPS)

1577
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:28,394
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1578
01:33:38,196 --> 01:33:41,658
(CLUNKING FOOTSTEPS,
MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

1579
01:33:41,741 --> 01:33:45,912
<i>Abby, you've been
a very, very bad girl.</i>

1580
01:33:47,831 --> 01:33:49,874
(WHIRRING)

1581
01:33:58,341 --> 01:33:59,968
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1582
01:34:01,094 --> 01:34:02,095
(THUDS)

1583
01:34:07,058 --> 01:34:08,643
(GRUNTS AND THUDS)

1584
01:34:08,726 --> 01:34:09,727
(COUGHS)

1585
01:34:10,562 --> 01:34:13,147
Where do you think
you're going, jackass?

1586
01:34:16,025 --> 01:34:17,610
(RAPID ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1587
01:34:24,826 --> 01:34:26,077
Chica.

1588
01:34:26,160 --> 01:34:28,204
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

1589
01:34:28,288 --> 01:34:30,582
(POWERING DOWN)

1590
01:34:30,665 --> 01:34:32,458
Oh. What's wrong
with them?

1591
01:34:32,542 --> 01:34:34,544
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1592
01:34:39,507 --> 01:34:43,177
Their systems,
they're... they're failing.

1593
01:34:43,261 --> 01:34:45,722
(HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING)

1594
01:34:51,102 --> 01:34:52,854
They weren't made
to leave Freddy's.

1595
01:34:53,438 --> 01:34:55,064
They're dying?

1596
01:34:56,482 --> 01:34:57,942
No way, you can't die.

1597
01:34:59,402 --> 01:35:01,362
BOY: We're just
moving on.

1598
01:35:03,615 --> 01:35:05,825
We can't stay
in those bodies anymore.

1599
01:35:11,164 --> 01:35:12,874
Are you going to heaven?

1600
01:35:15,126 --> 01:35:16,711
See you there someday?

1601
01:35:17,712 --> 01:35:18,963
But not too soon.

1602
01:35:21,049 --> 01:35:22,050
Mike?

1603
01:35:22,634 --> 01:35:25,219
Yeah? You should know
that when we leave...

1604
01:35:26,596 --> 01:35:28,222
I won't be able
to hold him anymore.

1605
01:35:29,557 --> 01:35:31,059
He'll get out
eventually,

1606
01:35:31,142 --> 01:35:33,019
and he'll be stronger
than before.

1607
01:35:33,978 --> 01:35:34,979
Who?

1608
01:35:35,063 --> 01:35:37,023
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1609
01:35:37,106 --> 01:35:38,441
(CRACKLING STOPS)

1610
01:35:41,653 --> 01:35:43,071
(STAMMERS)

1611
01:35:48,493 --> 01:35:49,494
Goodbye.

1612
01:35:49,577 --> 01:35:51,663
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

1613
01:35:54,332 --> 01:35:55,333
MIKE: (SOFTLY) Hey.

1614
01:36:02,674 --> 01:36:05,259
Mike? Whoa.

1615
01:36:07,887 --> 01:36:09,263
Everyone okay?

1616
01:36:11,182 --> 01:36:12,600
MIKE: Yeah, um...

1617
01:36:12,684 --> 01:36:14,769
Hey, we got to go.
Okay.

1618
01:36:14,852 --> 01:36:16,771
(ABBY SOBBING)
Come on, Abby.

1619
01:36:19,399 --> 01:36:20,566
Stay away from us.

1620
01:36:21,567 --> 01:36:22,568
What?

1621
01:36:25,071 --> 01:36:26,322
I can't trust you.

1622
01:36:26,823 --> 01:36:27,949
Mike...

1623
01:36:28,032 --> 01:36:29,033
Just stay away.

1624
01:36:31,619 --> 01:36:33,705
(SHORT, GASPING BREATHS)

1625
01:36:46,134 --> 01:36:48,136
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

1626
01:36:55,727 --> 01:36:57,562
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1627
01:36:59,939 --> 01:37:01,399
(MECHANICAL CLICKING)

1628
01:37:01,482 --> 01:37:03,568
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1629
01:37:04,819 --> 01:37:06,070
(MUSIC STOPS)

1630
01:37:06,154 --> 01:37:08,156
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

1631
01:37:08,239 --> 01:37:10,867
(MECHANICAL CLICKING)
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

1632
01:37:17,498 --> 01:37:19,500
<i>(IT'S BEEN SO LONG</i> BY THE
LIVING TOMBSTONE PLAYING)

1633
01:37:27,759 --> 01:37:29,719
(SINGING) <i>I don't know
what I was thinking</i>

1634
01:37:29,802 --> 01:37:32,096
<i>Leaving my child behind</i>

1635
01:37:32,180 --> 01:37:34,098
<i>Now I suffer the curse</i>

1636
01:37:34,182 --> 01:37:37,101
<i>And now I am blind</i>

1637
01:37:37,185 --> 01:37:39,854
<i>With all this anger,
guilt and sadness</i>

1638
01:37:39,937 --> 01:37:42,148
<i>Coming to haunt me forever</i>

1639
01:37:42,231 --> 01:37:43,941
<i>I can't wait for the cliff</i>

1640
01:37:44,025 --> 01:37:46,110
<i>At the end of the river</i>

1641
01:37:47,737 --> 01:37:49,655
<i>Is this revenge
I am seeking?</i>

1642
01:37:49,739 --> 01:37:52,116
<i>Or seeking someone
to avenge me?</i>

1643
01:37:52,200 --> 01:37:53,951
<i>Stuck in my own paradox</i>

1644
01:37:54,035 --> 01:37:56,037
<i>I wanna set myself free</i>

1645
01:37:57,121 --> 01:37:59,707
<i>Maybe I should
chase and find</i>

1646
01:37:59,791 --> 01:38:02,085
<i>Before they'll try
to stop it</i>

1647
01:38:02,168 --> 01:38:06,172
<i>It won't be long
before I'll become a puppet</i>

1648
01:38:07,256 --> 01:38:09,634
<i>It's been so long</i>

1649
01:38:09,717 --> 01:38:11,677
<i>Since I last
have seen my son</i>

1650
01:38:11,761 --> 01:38:13,221
<i>Lost to this monster</i>

1651
01:38:13,304 --> 01:38:16,224
<i>To the man
behind the slaughter</i>

1652
01:38:17,100 --> 01:38:19,519
<i>Since you've been gone</i>

1653
01:38:19,602 --> 01:38:21,562
<i>I've been singing
this stupid song</i>

1654
01:38:21,646 --> 01:38:23,397
<i>So I could ponder</i>

1655
01:38:23,481 --> 01:38:26,275
<i>The sanity of your mother</i>

1656
01:38:46,587 --> 01:38:47,588
(SONG ENDS)

1657
01:38:47,672 --> 01:38:49,257
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1658
01:39:07,108 --> 01:39:09,235
Why do we have
to do this in the rain?

1659
01:39:09,318 --> 01:39:10,987
Because this whole place is
getting demolished tomorrow.

1660
01:39:11,070 --> 01:39:13,322
We got to grab everything
we can while it's still here.

1661
01:39:13,406 --> 01:39:15,950
Why couldn't we just make
the props for the haunted house?

1662
01:39:16,033 --> 01:39:17,994
Come on, they want
the authentic thing.

1663
01:39:18,077 --> 01:39:20,580
The authentic
Fazbear experience.

1664
01:39:20,663 --> 01:39:22,331
You can't
replicate that.

1665
01:39:22,415 --> 01:39:23,791
Just try
looking around.

1666
01:39:23,875 --> 01:39:27,086
Anything that might trigger
a little bit of nostalgia.

1667
01:39:28,087 --> 01:39:30,381
Ethan! Where are you?

1668
01:39:30,464 --> 01:39:31,799
You got something?

1669
01:39:32,300 --> 01:39:33,676
ETHAN: (IN DISTANCE)
Back here!

1670
01:39:33,759 --> 01:39:36,804
Dude, I... I think I just
found another room.

1671
01:39:36,888 --> 01:39:38,973
I'm not joking. I think I
just found another room.

1672
01:39:39,056 --> 01:39:40,558
Get back here
right now!

1673
01:39:41,767 --> 01:39:43,311
Yes, Ethan!
ROBERT: Okay, okay, okay.

1674
01:39:45,188 --> 01:39:47,607
You got something?
I... Yeah.

1675
01:39:47,690 --> 01:39:49,066
I think
I found one. I...

1676
01:39:49,775 --> 01:39:51,402
(LAUGHING) I think
I found a real one.

1677
01:39:51,485 --> 01:39:52,945
(BOTH LAUGHING)

1678
01:39:53,905 --> 01:39:55,615
How is this
still here?

1679
01:39:56,407 --> 01:39:57,742
It smells terrible.

1680
01:40:00,369 --> 01:40:02,163
Yeah, we gotta
take this with us.

1681
01:40:02,246 --> 01:40:03,497
Let's see, uh...

1682
01:40:04,081 --> 01:40:05,791
Hey, uh, Patrick,
cover it.

1683
01:40:05,875 --> 01:40:07,418
Let's get the dolly.
Cover it, will you?

1684
01:40:07,501 --> 01:40:08,794
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
(ETHAN CLAPPING)

1685
01:40:08,878 --> 01:40:10,671
(ETHAN WHOOPING)

1686
01:40:23,976 --> 01:40:25,019
Hey, guys, wait up!

1687
01:40:28,022 --> 01:40:29,857
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1688
01:40:29,941 --> 01:40:31,943
(WIND BLOWING)

1689
01:40:43,329 --> 01:40:45,915
(ELECTRICAL CRACKLING)

1690
01:40:53,547 --> 01:40:55,508
(DEEP GROANING)

1691
01:40:57,927 --> 01:40:59,929
(UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING)

1692
01:43:17,608 --> 01:43:21,070
(CASSETTE TAPE CLATTERING)

1693
01:43:21,153 --> 01:43:22,321
(BUTTON CLICKS)
(TAPE WHIRRING)

1694
01:43:22,405 --> 01:43:24,073
HENRY: <i>Leaving dead space.</i>

1695
01:43:24,156 --> 01:43:27,576
<i>Three, two, one.</i>

1696
01:43:28,285 --> 01:43:30,621
<i>This message is intended
as a warning.</i>

1697
01:43:31,455 --> 01:43:33,457
<i>Mike, I wish
we'd had more time</i>

1698
01:43:33,541 --> 01:43:35,209
<i>after our conversation
about Charlotte,</i>

1699
01:43:35,292 --> 01:43:37,670
<i>but I'm sending you
this message now in case I...</i>

1700
01:43:39,255 --> 01:43:40,965
<i>I can't deliver it in person.</i>

1701
01:43:41,966 --> 01:43:44,009
<i>There are things
you need to be aware of.</i>

1702
01:43:44,552 --> 01:43:47,888
<i>I was William Afton's
business partner for many years.</i>

1703
01:43:47,972 --> 01:43:51,225
<i>And although the equipment I have
left over from that time is outdated,</i>

1704
01:43:51,308 --> 01:43:53,811
<i>I can still track
some of the animatronics.</i>

1705
01:43:54,395 --> 01:43:55,980
<i>Mike, the marionette...</i>

1706
01:43:56,063 --> 01:43:58,190
(RUSTLING)

1707
01:43:58,274 --> 01:44:00,234
<i>Mike, get out
as fast as you can.</i>

1708
01:44:00,317 --> 01:44:01,944
<i>She's coming for you.</i>
(STATIC DRONING)

1709
01:44:04,405 --> 01:44:05,573
(BUTTON CLICKS)
(WHIRRING STOPS)

